# qwen3:8b-fast -- Qwen 3 8B with chain-of-thought reasoning ("thinking") disabled.
#
# WHY THIS EXISTS
# ---------------
# Qwen3 models enable chain-of-thought reasoning by default.  Before
# generating a response (or a tool call), the model emits an internal
# <think>...</think> block.  This is valuable for complex reasoning tasks,
# but causes two concrete problems when qwen3:8b is used as an OpenCode
# agent driving tool calls:
#
#   1. The model spends its output-token budget on reasoning text instead
#      of emitting the tool call immediately.  With OpenCode's system
#      prompt + AGENTS.md + agent prompt + tool schemas already in context,
#      qwen3:8b sometimes exhausts its budget inside the think block and
#      never reaches the actual <tool_call> XML.
#
#   2. Ollama's OpenAI-compatible endpoint (/v1/chat/completions) silently
#      ignores the `think` request parameter.  The AI SDK adapter used by
#      OpenCode (@ai-sdk/openai-compatible) correctly passes `think: false`
#      in the HTTP body, but Ollama's /v1 layer discards it.  Only the
#      native /api/chat endpoint honours the parameter -- and the community
#      ollama-ai-provider package (which uses /api/chat) has a hardcoded
#      settings list that also omits `think`.
#
#   3. `PARAMETER think false` is not a valid Ollama Modelfile directive.
#      Ollama's PARAMETER instruction supports only sampling parameters
#      (temperature, top_k, stop, num_ctx, etc.).  `think` is a runtime
#      request field, not a model parameter.
#
# HOW THIS ACTUALLY WORKS
# -----------------------
# The Qwen3 chat template (visible via `ollama show qwen3:8b --modelfile`)
# controls thinking mode through two mechanisms in the prompt:
#
#   1. Appending `/no_think` to the last user message tells Qwen3 to
#      skip the reasoning phase for this turn.
#
#   2. Pre-filling the assistant response with an empty `<think></think>`
#      block forces the model past the thinking stage immediately, so it
#      proceeds directly to the actual response or tool call.
#
# The original template applies both only when the API request sets
# `think=false` (i.e. `$.IsThinkSet=true, $.Think=false`).  This
# derivative overrides the TEMPLATE to apply both unconditionally,
# making no-think the fixed default regardless of the API caller.
#
# DISK USAGE
# ----------
# Ollama stores models as content-addressable layers.  This derivative
# shares all weight blobs with qwen3:8b -- only a tiny config/template
# layer is added.  No disk space is duplicated.
#
# HOW TO REBUILD (manual)
# -----------------------
#   cd ~/Projects/ai-coding
#   ollama create qwen3:8b-fast -f ollama/qwen3-8b-fast.Modelfile
#
# Or use the helper script (handles guards and multi-model setup):
#   ./ollama/setup.sh
#
# FRESH MACHINE SETUP
# -------------------
# On a new machine, run in order:
#   1. ollama pull qwen3:8b          # pull the base weights (~5 GB)
#   2. ./ollama/setup.sh             # build all derivatives
#
# The home-manager activation script (home.activation.ensureOllamaModels
# in ~/Projects/home-manager/home.nix) calls setup.sh automatically on
# every `home-manager switch`, so step 2 is handled for you as long as
# Ollama is already running when you switch.
#
# ADDING MORE DERIVATIVES
# -----------------------
# To add another derivative model:
#   1. Create a new Modelfile in this directory following this pattern.
#   2. Add its name to the MODELS array in ollama/setup.sh.
#   3. Add the model ID to opencode/mappings/opencode.json.
#   4. Update docs/ollama-models.md with the new model's description.
#   5. Commit both repos and run `home-manager switch`.
#
# REFERENCE
# ---------
# Ollama Modelfile syntax:
#   https://github.com/ollama/ollama/blob/main/docs/modelfile.md
# Qwen3 thinking mode documentation:
#   https://qwenlm.github.io/blog/qwen3/#thinking-mode

FROM qwen3:8b

# Override the template to hardcode no-think mode.
#
# Changes vs the upstream qwen3:8b template:
#
#   USER MESSAGE (last turn only):
#     Original: conditionally appends `/no_think` when IsThinkSet=true, Think=false
#     This:     unconditionally appends `/no_think` to the last user message
#
#   ASSISTANT PREFIX (when model must respond):
#     Original: conditionally prefills `<think>\n\n</think>\n\n` when IsThinkSet=true, Think=false
#     This:     unconditionally prefills `<think>\n\n</think>\n\n`
#
# All other template logic (system prompt, tools, tool_response, multi-turn
# history) is identical to the upstream template.
TEMPLATE """
{{- $lastUserIdx := -1 -}}
{{- range $idx, $msg := .Messages -}}
{{- if eq $msg.Role "user" }}{{ $lastUserIdx = $idx }}{{ end -}}
{{- end }}
{{- if or .System .Tools }}<|im_start|>system
{{ if .System }}
{{ .System }}
{{- end }}
{{- if .Tools }}

# Tools

You may call one or more functions to assist with the user query.

You are provided with function signatures within <tools></tools> XML tags:
<tools>
{{- range .Tools }}
{"type": "function", "function": {{ .Function }}}
{{- end }}
</tools>

For each function call, return a json object with function name and arguments within <tool_call></tool_call> XML tags:
<tool_call>
{"name": <function-name>, "arguments": <args-json-object>}
</tool_call>
{{- end -}}
<|im_end|>
{{ end }}
{{- range $i, $_ := .Messages }}
{{- $last := eq (len (slice $.Messages $i)) 1 -}}
{{- if eq .Role "user" }}<|im_start|>user
{{ .Content }}
{{- if eq $i $lastUserIdx }} /no_think{{- end }}<|im_end|>
{{ else if eq .Role "assistant" }}<|im_start|>assistant
{{ if (and $.IsThinkSet (and .Thinking (or $last (gt $i $lastUserIdx)))) -}}
<think>{{ .Thinking }}</think>
{{ end -}}
{{ if .Content }}{{ .Content }}
{{- else if .ToolCalls }}<tool_call>
{{ range .ToolCalls }}{"name": "{{ .Function.Name }}", "arguments": {{ .Function.Arguments }}}
{{ end }}</tool_call>
{{- end }}{{ if not $last }}<|im_end|>
{{ end }}
{{- else if eq .Role "tool" }}<|im_start|>user
<tool_response>
{{ .Content }}
</tool_response><|im_end|>
{{ end }}
{{- if and (ne .Role "assistant") $last }}<|im_start|>assistant
<think>

</think>

{{ end }}
{{- end }}"""

PARAMETER stop <|im_start|>
PARAMETER stop <|im_end|>
PARAMETER temperature 0.6
PARAMETER top_k 20
PARAMETER top_p 0.95
PARAMETER repeat_penalty 1
